definition.value: An alpha-D-glucosyl-(1->4)-D-mannopyranose in which the anomeric hydroxy group has alpha configuration.
A heptenedioic acid that is hept-2-enedioic acid substituted by oxo groups at positions 4 and 6.
A D-tagatofuranose 6-phosphate with an alpha-configuration at the anomeric position.
A D-tagatose 6-phosphate that is in the open-chain keto-form.
The alpha anomer of D-fructofuranuronic acid.
The beta anomer of D-fructofuranuronic acid.
The straight-chain keto form of D-fructuronic acid.

A member of the class of  bilenes that is red chlorophyll catabolite in which a methylene group is introduced at position 1 via the reduction of a double bond. It is an intermediate of chlorophyll breakdown in plants.
A D-glucuronic acid in cyclic pyranose form.
A D-galactopyranuronic acid with a beta-configuration at the anomeric center.
Any primary amide having its amide oxygen replaced by sulfur.
An agonist that selectively binds to and activates a nicotinic acetylcholine receptor.
A 5-hydroxypenta-2,4-diene-1,2,5-tricarboxylic acid in which the double bond geometry is specified as (2E,4Z).
A simplest memebr of the class of aurones that is 1-benzofuran-3(2H)-one in which both hydrogens at position 2 are substituted by a benzylidene group (the Z-isomer).
A D-glucosamine whose structure comprises D-glucopyranose having an amino substituent at position 2.

A monocarboxylic acid amide that is N,N-diethylprop-2-enamide in which the hydrogen at position 2 is substituted by a cyano group and the hydrogen at the 3E position is substituted by a 3,4-dihydroxy-5-nitrophenyl group.
An aspartic acid derivative having a 3-methyl substituent.
